text.tspan: DC590+ DRV Series DC Digital Drive
All connections made to terminal blocks A, B and C must be isolated signal voltages. Never perform high voltage resistance or dielectric
strength tests without first completely disconnecting the drive from the circuit being tested.
To complywith EMC requirements, use screened control cables with a minimum cross-section areaof 0.75mm
Control wiring should be bundled and routed to the left side of the drive so that the control door on Frames 3, 4, 5 & H is free to open.
